{
  "texts": [
    "To assess the critical pixel number of the SLM, it is essential to explore two distinct scenarios, as diagramed in Fig. 6a, b.",
    "The first scenario involves variations in the number of pixels while keeping the physical dimensions of the layers fixed.",
    "Alternatively, the second scenario considers changes in the number of pixels while maintaining the pixel dimensions, which, in turn, alter the physical dimensions of the layers.",
    "In the first scenario, our primary focus is on the influence of pixel density or sampling precision on quantum gates.",
    "Our analysis intuitively suggests that higher pixel densities contribute to enhanced quantum gate performance."
  ]
}